        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 12:22PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 1221 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Bronson to near Rome City. Movement was
east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Angola, Lagrange, Bronson, Fremont, Hamilton, Reading, Edon,
Columbia, Ray, Kinderhook, Fawn River, California, Wolcottville,
Ashley, Burr Oak, Gilead, Hudson, Camden, Orland, and Montgomery.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 69 in Indiana between mile markers 339 and 357.
Interstate 69 in Michigan between mile markers 1 and 8.
Interstate 80 in Indiana between mile markers 123 and 156.
Interstate 80 in Ohio between mile markers 0 and 5.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
